`,n(e.p,{children:["It depends. If you are coming from React, porting your components to Qwik should be straight forward. But on top of that, thanks to ",n(e.a,{href:"/docs/integrations/react/",children:n(e.code,{children:"Qwik React"})}),", you can use all of the React ecosystem, so you can use any of your React components, and any React library in a Qwik app."]}),`
`,n(e.h2,{id:"can-i-enjoy-the-rich-react-ecosystem",children:[n(e.a,{"aria-hidden":"true",tabindex:"-1",href:"#can-i-enjoy-the-rich-react-ecosystem",children:n(e.span,{class:"icon icon-link"})}),"Can I enjoy the rich React ecosystem?"]}),`
`,n(e.p,{children:["Yes! Qwik can run React components natively, ",n(e.a,{href:"/docs/integrations/react/",children:"check out the docs"}),"."]}),`
`,n(e.p,{children:"You will be amazed!"}),`
`,n(e.h2,{id:"does-qwik-do-partial-hydration",children:[n(e.a,{"aria-hidden":"true",tabindex:"-1",href:"#does-qwik-do-partial-hydration",children:n(e.span,{class:"icon icon-link"})}),"Does Qwik do partial hydration?"]}),`
`,n(e.p,{children:["No. Partial hydration (or island architecture), popularized by ",n(e.a,{href:"https://astro.build/",children:"Astro"}),", is about breaking the app into islands of interactivity to avoid ",n(e.a,{href:"https://www.builder.io/blog/hydration-is-pure-overhead",children:"full-page hydration"}),", where all existing components in the page need to be downloaded and executed."]}),`
`,n(e.p,{children:"For this to work, developers need to manually define the islands, and then manually describe in which situations they should be hydrated. The islands also cannot communicate with each other."}),`
`,n(e.p,{children:"Instead, Qwik components do not hydrate at all. Qwik achieves this through a powerful serialization system that serializes only the necessary state in the reactivity graph. This way, the app can resume without eagerly running any JS."}),`
`,n(e.p,{children:"We think resumability scales without the negative trade-offs of partial hydration."}),`
`,n(e.h2,{id:"in-which-languages-is-qwik-written",children:[n(e.a,{"aria-hidden":"true",tabindex:"-1",href:"#in-which-languages-is-qwik-written",children:n(e.span,{class:"icon icon-link"})}),"In which languages is Qwik written?"]}),`
`,n(e.p,{children:"Most of Qwik is written in TypeScript, a superset of JavaScript that adds optional static typing and other features. However, the Qwik compiler (or optimizer) is written in Rust, a language that is very fast and memory efficient."}),`
`,n(e.h2,{id:"does-qwik-have-a-community",children:[n(e.a,{"aria-hidden":"true",tabindex:"-1",href:"#does-qwik-have-a-community",children:n(e.span,{class:"icon icon-link"})}),"Does Qwik have a community?"]}),`
`,n(e.p,{children:["Yes! there is a growing community of Qwik developers at ",n(e.a,{href:"https://qwik.builder.io/chat",children:"Discord"})," and ",n(e.a,{href:"https://github.com/BuilderIO/qwik",children:"GitHub"}),". They are making amazing contributions to the framework, building sites at scale, and helping each other. ",n(e.a,{href:"https://qwik.builder.io/chat",children:"Join us"}),"."]}),`
`,n(e.h2,{id:"is-qwik-production-ready",children:[n(e.a,{"aria-hidden":"true",tabindex:"-1",href:"#is-qwik-production-ready",children:n(e.span,{class:"icon icon-link"})}),"Is Qwik production ready?"]}),`
`,n(e.p,{children:"Yes! Qwik is already at version 1.1. Qwik has been in development for 3 years now. We are confident that Qwik is ready for production, and there are no expected breaking changes."}),`
`,n(e.p,{children:[n(e.a,{href:"https://www.builder.io/",children:"Builder.io"})," and a lot of teams are already using Qwik in production, so you will not be alone."]}),`
`,n(e.h2,{id:"is-it-true-that-qwik-serializes-too-much-data-in-the-html",children:[n(e.a,{"aria-hidden":"true",tabindex:"-1",href:"#is-it-true-that-qwik-serializes-too-much-data-in-the-html",children:n(e.span,{class:"icon icon-link"})}),"Is it true that Qwik serializes too much data in the HTML?"]}),`
